"36:65:8" : {s: 36, a: 65, w: 8, r: "رجل", t: "أَرْجُلُهُم", l: "رِجْل", lc: 15, tl: "arjuluhum", lb: "পা",e: "their feet", b: "তাদের পা গুলো", i: "kaki-kaki mereka", f: 1, rm: "to go on foot, urge with foot, walk, tie by the feet, let (a female) suckle her young, be curly (hair), set free with his mother. rajjala - to comfort anyone, comb the hair, grant a respite. tarajjala - to go down without rope. rijlatun - vigour in walking. rijlun - foot, soldiers, good walker, tramp. arajil - hunters, pedestrian. rajulun - male human being, man, a person with heir. rajilun - foot, footmen (slow walkers). rijlain - two feet. arjul (pl.) - feet.", ag: "أسم مرفوع وضمير متصل ", eg: "Noun Nominative case and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "NOM", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "F", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "أَرْجُلٌۭ،رِجَالٌۭ،رَجُلٌۭ،رَجُلَانِ"},
