"36:66:5" : {s: 36, a: 66, w: 5, r: "عين", t: "أَعْيُنِهِمْ", l: "عَيْن", lc: 57, tl: "aʿyunihim", lb: "চোখ",e: "their eyes", b: "তাদের চক্ষুদীপ গুলোকে", i: "penglihatan mata mereka", f: 2, rm: "to hurt in the eye, smite anyone with the evil eye, flow tears, become a spy. Aayan - to view, face. Ainun - eye, look, hole, but of a tree, spy, middle letter of a trilateral word, spring of water, chief, personage of a place. Ayan (pl. Inun): lovely, wide-eyed, lovely black eyed. Maiinun - water, spring.", ag: "أسم مجرور وضمير متصل ", eg: "Noun Genitive case and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "GEN", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "F", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "أَعْيُنٌۭ"},
